title: 820- 00165 No booting, Fan spin
message:
Do you get steady light on USB mouse?
You can also use a pendrive with macOS preinstalled.
If Link LED flashes, USB activity is 100% confirmed.

I prefer this, as no problems turning boad on/off many times,
[url]http://www.cmizapper.com/products/usb-tester.html[/url]

title: 820- 00165 No booting, Fan spin
message: Mouse don't light when i connect in USB, still the same with pendrive with macOS. Thanks i buy chipmunk. What I can do next?

title: 820- 00165 No booting, Fan spin
message:
No reason to search for video, as the board doesn't boot.

Check all SPI Bus Termination resistors and their traces.
Clean J6100; remove it, if you don't use Medusa programmer.

Be sure PLT_RESET_L goes steady high.
Try known good BIOS.
